---
// About.astro - Explains what Bomfather is and its purpose
---

<section class="py-16 bg-light-blue">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold font-heading mb-6 text-center">What is Bomfather?</h2>
    
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="bg-light-gray border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-sm p-8 w-full">
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          <strong>Bomfather</strong> is an advanced security tool that creates <strong>Runtime AI Bills of Materials (Runtime-AIBOMs)</strong> and provides active protection for AI systems. 
          Unlike static approaches that only assess files and configurations at build time, Bomfather captures information in the kernel in real-time.
        </p>
        
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          Modern AI systems often operate as "opaque systems," revealing little about critical components. Bomfather leverages eBPF 
          to monitor system calls at the kernel level, creating a comprehensive audit log for every component and runtime change during AI training and fine-tuning.
        </p>
        
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">Two Core Capabilities</h3>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-6">
          <!-- Runtime-AIBOM Section -->
          <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Runtime AI Bills of Materials</h3>
            <p class="text-lg mb-3">
              Bomfather creates comprehensive Runtime-AIBOMs that provide cryptographic proof of an AI system's composition:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-lg space-y-2">
              <li>Captures the <strong>complete runtime environment</strong></li>
              <li>Provides <strong>tamper-evident verification</strong></li>
              <li>Creates an <strong>audit trail of all activities</strong></li>
              <li>Follows Zero Trust Architecture (ZTA)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Active Protection Section -->
          <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Active Protection</h3>
            <p class="text-lg mb-3">
              Bomfather goes beyond passive monitoring by actively preventing malicious accesses:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-lg space-y-2">
              <li>Users specify which files they <strong>trust</strong></li>
              <li><strong>Blocks unauthorized access</strong> in real-time</li>
              <li>Allows legitimate workflows to <strong>continue normally</strong></li>
              <li>Uses a secure <strong>"default-deny" principle</strong></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section> 